<br>
Well the other day I stumbled into an AEgroup that literally just made me go, &quot;holy crap, this is nuts&quot;.  Some of you might have been doing this for awhile but I have never heard of or seen this.<br>
<br>
Basically picture this, AE group consisting of 1 shaman, and 2 mages, thats it.  In this group we were hunting in FG and pulling about 15-20 shrooms/underbulks/dregs etc at a time, and AEing them like mad.  Downtime after kills, approx 5 minutes downtime before next pull started !<br>
<br>
In approx 7 hours of Aeing this way spread over 2 days, none of us ever died once, nor even came close to it ! I usually on average get hit maybe 10 times during the course for the AE and lose maybe like 2 bubs hp tops..<br>
<br>
It works like this, shammy goes out and pulls like mad with slow building up aggro, rounds up the mobs and brings back to group.  AE like mad, dead.. Whats strange is I thought we would've gotten complete aggro off shaman after like the first or second AE, but sometimes we never get hit once, and usually just get hit randomly like a few times, so it seems Shaman holds aggro pretty well.  Also if we ever lose hp, shaman instantly just heals us back to full..<br>
<br>
After fight mages mod2 to FM while shaman Torpors.  Then mages drop mods for shaman.  Roughly 5 min sometimes 10 downtime after fight.<br>
<br>
It is just another alternative to your typical AE groups that I sure as heck never realized was possible.  And the few mages I asked the second day to join all said the same thing &quot;uh, you can't AE without an enchanter&quot; &quot;where is everyone else ? on the way ?&quot; &quot;we are going to die&quot;... heh heh<br>
<br>
Anyway hopefully someone might give this a shot, lot easier to find a 60 shaman and another mage then it is to put together a 6 person AE group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyone else done this ? Or had other &quot;different&quot; AE group experiences ??<br>
